o4-mini Answer:
To compute \(C(12,4)\), use the formula
\[
\binom{12}{4} = \frac{12!}{4!\,8!}
= \frac{12 \times 11 \times 10 \times 9}{4 \times 3 \times 2 \times 1}
= \frac{11880}{24}
= 495.
\]
So, \(C(12,4)=495\).

o3 Answer:
The binomial coefficient \(C(7,6)\) (read “7 choose 6”) is

\(C(7,6) = \dfrac{7!}{6!\,(7-6)!}
         = \dfrac{7!}{6!\,1!}
         = \dfrac{7 \cdot 6!}{6!\,1}
         = 7.\)

Therefore,
\(C(7,6) = 7.\)
